In this article, President Donald J. Trump proclaims September 11th as Patriot Day in honor of the nearly 3,000 lives lost on that day in 2001. He pays tribute to the heroes who sacrificed their lives and helped others during the tragedy. The article also highlights the resilience and unity of Americans in the face of adversity. The President urges Americans to thank service members and first responders who are fighting against terrorism and to participate in community service to honor those who were lost. The article concludes with a call to observe a moment of silence at 8:46 a.m., the time the first plane struck the World Trade Center.